v:4 c:$ m:portfolio role:dev x:vue-form-supabase-rls
gate: LOCKED

task: Build the Contact room — a friendly form that writes to Supabase contact_msgs (S01/T04 schema) via an edge function. Includes anti-spam (Turnstile or honeypot), success animation, and links to Telegram/LinkedIn/GitHub from CV.

requires: [vue, supabase]
out:
  - app/src/rooms/contact/room.config.ts
  - app/src/rooms/contact/Room.vue
  - app/src/rooms/contact/ContactForm.vue
  - app/src/rooms/contact/SuccessSplash.vue
  - app/src/rooms/contact/useContactSubmit.ts
  - portfolio/supabase/functions/submit-contact/index.ts (edge function)
  - portfolio/supabase/migrations/0003_contact_rls.sql

room-manifest:
  - slug: 'contact'
  - title: 'Contact'
  - summary: 'Drop a line — Telegram, GitHub, LinkedIn, or just leave a message.'
  - tags: ['fullstack', 'forms']
  - skillsDemoed: ['fullstack']

form-fields:
  - name (required, 2-80)
  - email (required, RFC-light validation)
  - body (required, 10-2000)
  - honeypot field "company_url" (must stay empty)

submit-flow:
  - Client validates → POST to /functions/v1/submit-contact with anon key.
  - Edge function: re-validate, check honeypot, rate-limit by IP (5/hour), insert with service-role.
  - Success: SuccessSplash with GSAP burst (uses core-dot flash from glass-entity T03).
  - Error: inline error, form preserved.

constraints:
  - contact_msgs RLS: NO direct anon insert (only edge function with service-role).
  - Rate limit: in-memory or via Supabase counter table (decide in DEV).
  - Honeypot is the primary anti-spam (Turnstile deferred unless abuse seen).
  - Email NOT required to be deliverable (just well-formed).
  - GDPR-light: footnote "Stored to reply, never shared."

socials-row (above form):
  - Telegram: t.me/denistka
  - GitHub: github.com/denistka
  - LinkedIn: linkedin.com/in/denisbaranov
  - Email: mailto:denistka@gmail.com
  - All as glass-entity buttons with hover wash.

done:
  - Submit success path: form → edge fn → row in contact_msgs → splash → reset.
  - Honeypot filled: silently fakes success, no DB write (logged for analysis).
  - 6th submission within an hour from same IP returns 429.
  - Reduced-motion: success animation degraded to fade only.
  - Direct table-insert from anon key REJECTED (RLS verified in Studio).
